Backstab Watch - <img src="http://www.spasalon.com/templeofdawn/pictures/backstab.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ufaydetblaque.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fayde TBlaque</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/7/01 12:06:28 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://home.swbell.net/fayde01/order1.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Changes to what we are proposing to Evade +more.</span><hr size=1> Evade: The moving the rogue from the #1 spot to between the #2 and #3 spot(which basically means moving from #1 to #2 with flowery language), is not the solution to this situation.  When evade was originally introduced, the rogue was dropped to the bottom of the hate list, and was working as intended.  Now the hate list has expanded, and the rogue drops to the bottom still.  This is viewed as unbalancing?  The obvious solition would be to move the rogue to the spot where he/she woulda been at pre-expanded hate list. and i highly doubt that is between #2 and #3.  <br>
<br>
People that play rogues(pre-evade, and after) know their class, know what is going to happen in situations.  Telling these rogues that you are going to change the evade skill as you have stated, they know what effect it will have on them.  The effect may not be overnight.  The efect may not be as drastic as many have stated, but by using extream examples, people are trying to make a point.<br>
<br>
-The 3 rogue death spiral example is very real in 'raid/uber mob' situations.<br>
-Rogues being moved to 'nukers attack at 50% health' status is maybe a stretch, but i can see it being about 75% in reality.<br>
-Limiting rogues to 1 or 2 per raid, that reminds me alot of the whole 'manastone' situation from last year; when limiting players invited to raids was based solely on 1 reason (then it was if you had a 'manastone', now its 'inefficent' to have to 'res' the rogues after each fight).<br>
<br>
one thing i think should be considered, have the 'Hide/Evade' timer affected by 'haste/level', so that evade would be at the same rate as backstab, allowing rogues the ability to evade when it is most important for them to (right after a backstab attempt).<br>
<br>
Sneak and Hide:  Having 'Sneak and Hide' be active 'thru zoning,' 'linkdead,' and 'logout/in' is one of the most requested things i see after the whole Evade thing.  I would like to add my voice to the crowd.  I think this would be a wonderful addition to the game.  It would allow rogues a higher survival rate when scouting and going linkdead, when traveling(in PvP situations mainly).  I feel it would be good for the game while not causing any negitive effects to any class.<br>
<br>
Backstab and Instill Doubt:  The linking of these keys has always been a strange situation.  Having them be 'greyed out' when the other is pressed would be ok if a couple stipulations were allowed.  <br>
<br>
-Backstab button should be allowed to work if the 'Instill' fails, without having to wait for the 'Instill timer.'  As it works now, after you fail an 'Instill,' you can 'backstab' as soon as you see the 'your not scaring anybody' message.<br>
-The 'Instill timer' should be affected by 'haste/level' in the same way as the 'backstab timer' is. this would allow the 'grey out' time to be constant.<br>
-Intill skill should not have to go thru 'skill check,' 'kick hit/miss check,' and finally a 'fear check' for a successful try.  1 check should be all that is needed.<br>
<br>
thanks for your time.<br>
<br>
PS: to the comment about 'reviewing your equipment setup/damage output'  .....<br>
<br>
/auction looking to buy dragoon dirk!!  i deal too much damage need ot reequip to stay alive.<br>
