<br>
The big picture is -- the damage that rogues do.<br>
I was wondering when this was coming into play, and after reading post after post, and Kendrick's reply -- it came to me.<br>
<br>
Make evade less effective, and you make rogues less able to do damage.<br>
<br>
&quot;We looked at Rogues, saw an oversight in the way Evade worked, and we proposed a change that will not in any way ruin the class, nor make them less powerful, but will make them responsible for more of their damage output.&quot;<br>
<br>
Maybe I'm reading it wrong but, if evade is less likely to remove you off the hate list for a certain period of time, you're less able to do the damage you could pre-nerf.<br>
<br>
The short of it is, it's a reduction in the ability of a rogue to deal out damage. Plain and simple.<br>
