<br>
I think the reason for this is twofold; MOBs only check the hate list every few seconds, and sometimes they decide to stick with there current target instead of going off to attack the guy on the top of the list (particulary if thier current target is low AC and health).<br>
<br>
As to the proposed changes, as they are currently defined they will lead to a rogue not being able to safely do more than maybe 5 to 10% more damage than the main tank, in any size group.<br>
<br>
This is an insignificant difference - in every case a group or raid would be better off with another warrior, monk, paladin, shadowknight, ranger, mage or necro.  All of whom will do an indistinguishable amount of damage, but can not only tank a hell of a lot better (assuming the caps from test, and maybe excluding ranger), but also all have some useful utility, pulling or secondary healing powers as well.<br>
<br>
This means that, for the only group slot a rogue can compete for, we will become the 8th best class. <br>
<br>
If a rogue isn't needed for utility reasons (i.e. pickpocket, _maybe_ disarm traps), then they will be soloing.<br>
<br>
I notice that the one positive change lited for rogues is to bind wounds, which will actually enable well-equipped rogues to solo (though we we still be the worst soloing class, equal worst healer, 3rd or 4th worst main tank).<br>
<br>
I think if these changes see the live servers, we will be doing that a lot.<br>
